{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Homelab 101","date":"09 September 2019","path":"/homelab","author":"Nate Wood","excerpt":"An intro to homelab - what is it and why you should have one","tags":["homelab","DC402"],"coverImage":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":1.7777777777777777,"src":"/static/d8050877f7f815b5d29551dc75821e76/bc3a8/datacenter.jpg","srcSet":"/static/d8050877f7f815b5d29551dc75821e76/d278e/datacenter.jpg 200w,\n/static/d8050877f7f815b5d29551dc75821e76/8539d/datacenter.jpg 400w,\n/static/d8050877f7f815b5d29551dc75821e76/bc3a8/datacenter.jpg 800w,\n/static/d8050877f7f815b5d29551dc75821e76/81ef8/datacenter.jpg 1200w","sizes":"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px"}}}},"id":"9fee39e4-bc61-5809-9b88-275271408eb0","html":"<hr>\n<h3>What is a homelab?</h3>\n<p>It's a collection of computer hardware and software typically used for learning or self-hosting  </p>\n<h3>Why build a homelab?</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Learning experience outside of school or work</li>\n<li>Can help with getting a job </li>\n<li><strong>It's fun!</strong>  </li>\n</ul>\n<h3>What can I do with it?</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Learn to use or administer new operating systems/equipment</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Linux distributions like Ubuntu, CentOS, or Kali</li>\n<li>Windows Server and related services like Active Directory or certificate management</li>\n<li>Networking and firewall </li>\n<li>Virtualization platforms such as ESXi, ProxMox, Hyper-V</li>\n<li>Container technology like Docker, Kuberneties  </li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Run enterprise grade hardware or software</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Many enterprise software suites have a community edition available</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Run a game server for your friends  </p>\n<ul>\n<li>The dedicated host will allow you to not use your own resource running the game locally </li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Media server</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Host your own digital library of home movies and photos with friends and family</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Storage server</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Who needs DropBox or Google Drive if you have your own cloud file hosting service</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Web hosting </p>\n<ul>\n<li>Host your own blog or services  </li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Is it expensive?</strong></h3>\n<p>It doesn't have to be - but if you're anything like myself you will eventually spend more money on the homelab :)  </p>\n<h4>Hardware</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>You don't need to have a full server rack to be able to take advantage of a homelab </li>\n<li>A <a href=\"https://www.raspberrypi.org/products/raspberry-pi-4-model-b/\">Rasberry Pi</a> or similar is sufficient to run a small Linux server or host  </li>\n</ul>\n<p><a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/628a5110c683405771ca2e79d4dffd44/6cd91/raspberryPi2.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 800px;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 133.33333333333331%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    ></span>\n    <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Raspberry Pi Small Homelab\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/628a5110c683405771ca2e79d4dffd44/b9a50/raspberryPi2.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/628a5110c683405771ca2e79d4dffd44/d336c/raspberryPi2.jpg 200w,\n/static/628a5110c683405771ca2e79d4dffd44/9c499/raspberryPi2.jpg 400w,\n/static/628a5110c683405771ca2e79d4dffd44/b9a50/raspberryPi2.jpg 800w,\n/static/628a5110c683405771ca2e79d4dffd44/6cd91/raspberryPi2.jpg 1008w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n      />\n  </span>\n  </a></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Start small and let it grow into an uncontrollable hobby :D d\n<a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/e86eb39a5db1e5c8d6fb70fa44d6cd84/e57ba/muffinStorage.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 800px;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 113.8804457953394%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    ></span>\n    <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"MonsterMuffin Storage\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/e86eb39a5db1e5c8d6fb70fa44d6cd84/b9a50/muffinStorage.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/e86eb39a5db1e5c8d6fb70fa44d6cd84/d336c/muffinStorage.jpg 200w,\n/static/e86eb39a5db1e5c8d6fb70fa44d6cd84/9c499/muffinStorage.jpg 400w,\n/static/e86eb39a5db1e5c8d6fb70fa44d6cd84/b9a50/muffinStorage.jpg 800w,\n/static/e86eb39a5db1e5c8d6fb70fa44d6cd84/e57ba/muffinStorage.jpg 987w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n      />\n  </span>\n  </a></li>\n</ul>\n<h4>What about the cloud?</h4>\n<p>Cloud providers typically provide free use for a short period of time - take full advantage of the free compute and storage if you can. </p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://aws.amazon.com/free/?all-free-tier.sort-by=item.additionalFields.SortRank&#x26;all-free-tier.sort-order=asc\">AWS</a> – 12 months</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://azure.microsoft.com/en-us/free/free-account-faq/\">Azure</a> – 12 months - $200 to spend in first 30 days</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://cloud.google.com/free/\">Google Compute</a> – 12 months - $300 credit with new accounts</li>\n</ul>\n<hr>\n<p><strong>This was presented at DC402 on September 10th, 2019</strong><br>\nThank you to <a href=\"https://dc402.org/\">DEF CON 402</a> for this opportunity to present. </p>","excerpt":"What is a homelab?It's a collection of computer hardware and software typically used for learning or self-hosting  Why build a homelab…"}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"type":"posts","next":{"frontmatter":{"path":"/hello","title":"Hello","tags":["hello world"]},"fileAbsolutePath":"C:/Users/Nate/git-repos/blog/src/posts/hello.md"},"previous":null}}